==Demographics==
At the 2020 census there were 1,163 people across 487 total housing units in the CDP with an occupancy rate of 99%. 907 were 18 years and over, making up 78% of the population. The racial makeup of the CDP was 93.1% White, 0.5% African American, 0.2% Native American, 0.61% Asian, 0% Pacific Islander, 1.29% from other races, and 2.45% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 3.4%.<ref>{{Cite web |title=USA Census 2020 Redistricting Census Designated Places (CDPs) Map Viewer |url=https://www.arcgis.com/apps/mapviewer/index.html?layers=77b64a0e30434c92b80267086dd87eea |access-date=2024-05-09 |website=www.arcgis.com}}</ref>

